The paper deals with multi-agent systems, which is a topic covered in the cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) sub-category. The use of game-theoretic frameworks suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) sub-category. The investigation of how to influence the behavior of uncontrollable agents through controlled agents involves the use of AI techniques, which could place the paper in the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. The paper also deals with control theory, which is covered in the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category. Finally, the examination of the effectiveness of different methods suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category.
